					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/marqfja87" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1895233); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1895233&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252423" alt="MarqFJA87" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1895233)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/marqfja87" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1895233); return false;" >MarqFJA87</a></span> <span class="odate time_1452370959 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Jan 2016 20:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2436983">
									

<p>I wonder if the titles for each tale has any significance for the SCP-001 proposal they're about. Of interest is that they're all Latin words.</p>
<ul>
<li>Clavis (The Gate Guardian): &quot;key; lever or bar for tightening a screw press&quot;.</li>
<li>Corvus (The Legacy): &quot;crow&quot;.</li>
<li>Cygnus (The Database): &quot;swan; (figurative) a poet, especially one who sings&quot;.</li>
<li>Lux (The Factory): &quot;light&quot;.</li>
<li>Pila (Sheaf of Papers): both &quot;mortar&quot; and &quot;pillar; pier&quot; (etymologically unrelated homophones).</li>
<li>Rota (The Prototype): &quot;wheel; (pars pro toto) a car, a chariot; (figuratively) the disc of the sun&quot;.</li>
<li>Virr (The Spiral Path): Seems to be a misspelling of <em><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/vir#Latin">vir</a></em>, meaning &quot;male human, man; man (human); grown man; brave man, hero; husband; (in military contexts) footsoldier&quot;.</li>
<li>Visium (The Foundation): Probably derived from <em><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/visus">visus</a></em> &#8212; The action of looking; the power of sight; a vision, sight, apparition; appearance &#8212; by combining it with the suffix <em>-ium</em>.</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
					
