<p>Just stumbled upon an interesting fact about the word &quot;cactus&quot;. It's Latin, right? But it's not <strong>native</strong> to Latin, but rather a <strong>loanword</strong> from Ancient Greek <em><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%CE%BA%CE%AC%CE%BA%CF%84%CE%BF%CF%82#Ancient_Greek">kaktos</a></em>, which at the time was used to refer to the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cardoon">cardoon</a>, whose binomial name is <em>Cynara cardunculus</em>.</p>
<p>So&#8230; &quot;Cynara&quot;, or &quot;Cardunculus&quot;?</p>

